  "id": "CHAR_calder_hurne",
  "label": "Calder Hurne",
  "description": "This individual is an undead remnant, preserved by the mineral chill typical of long interment in hollowed glass-veins. Gray eyes sit deep beneath a brow fixed in rigor, and pale skin clings tightly to the cheekbones and jaw, exposing a permanent architecture of bone. Brown hair remains in sparse, brittle lengths, with a receded hairline and a dry scalp sheen that reads as long dead tissue rather than age. The body is lean and desiccated, the hands elongated and tendon-prominent, marked by fine fissures and permanent stiffness in the knuckles.",
